Common Export Mistakes Businesses Should Avoid
One of the biggest mistakes exporters make is assuming any wooden crate is acceptable for international shipping. Untreated or unstamped wood packaging can lead to shipment refusal. Another issue is reusing old crates that no longer meet ISPM-15 export quality standards. Working with experienced Las Vegas crate manufacturers helps avoid errors by ensuring proper crate fabrication, correct stamping, and documentation. Trusted crate specialists Las Vegas also verify that reused crates remain compliant before export.

